---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="description" content="Professional elevation certificate services in Utah. FEMA-compliant surveys for flood insurance and building permits." />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width" />
    <link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/favicon.svg" />
    <title>{siteName} - Professional Elevation Survey Services</title>
  </head>
  <body>
    <Header siteName={siteName} navItems={navItems} />

    <main>
      <Hero
        title="FEMA Elevation Certificates For Flood Insurance"
        description="Professional engineers and surveyors providing FEMA Elevation Certificates to homeowners living in high-risk flood areas."
        primaryCTA={{ text: 'Get Started', href: '#contact' }}
        variant="centered"
      />

      <FeatureCards features={features} />

      <ContentSection
        title="Still waiting for flood insurance?"
        ctaText="Get Started"
        ctaHref="#contact"
      >
        <p>
          The FEMA elevation certificate process can be complicated and
          time-consuming, leading to delays in obtaining flood insurance. Many
          homeowners experience frustration waiting for their certificates while
          trying to close on loans or renew insurance policies.
        </p>
        <p>
          Our streamlined process with experienced engineers and surveyors
          eliminates these delays. With offices throughout Utah and the region,
          we provide fast, accurate FEMA elevation certificates that meet all
          insurance and lender requirements. Stop waiting and get the coverage
          you need with our efficient 2-week turnaround time.
        </p>
      </ContentSection>

      <section id="process">
        <ProcessSteps
          title="FEMA Elevation Certificates in Three Easy Steps"
          description="Our simple process gets you certified quickly and accurately"
          steps={processSteps}
        />
      </section>

      <ContentSection
        title="Why Jones & DeMille Engineering?"
        ctaText="Get Started"
        ctaHref="#contact"
        backgroundColor="bg-gray-50"
      >
        <p>
          utahelevationcertificate.com is owned and operated by Jones & DeMille
          Engineering, Inc., bringing decades of experience with FEMA projects
          and elevation certificates. Our streamlined process and professional
          approach ensure cost savings and peace of mind for every client.
        </p>
        <p>
          We are licensed engineers serving multiple states across the Western
          United States, including Utah, Wyoming, Arizona, Nevada, Colorado, New
          Mexico, California, Idaho, and Texas. This multi-state expertise means
          we understand regional requirements and can efficiently serve
          properties throughout the Intermountain West and beyond.
        </p>
      </ContentSection>

      <section id="team">
        <TeamSection
          title="Meet Our Experts"
          description="Our team of licensed professionals brings specialized expertise in FEMA elevation certificates"
          teamMembers={teamMembers}
        />
      </section>

      <section id="faq">
        <FAQ
          title="Frequently Asked Questions"
          description="Common questions about elevation certificates"
          faqs={faqs}
        />
      </section>

      <section id="contact">
        <ContactForm
          siteName="utahelevationcertificate"
          title="Request Your Elevation Certificate"
          description="Fill out the form below to get started"
          includeFileUpload={false}
        />
      </section>
    </main>

    <Footer
      siteName={siteName}
      companyName={companyName}
      footerLinks={[
        { label: 'Privacy Policy', href: '/privacy' },
        { label: 'Terms of Service', href: '/terms' }
      ]}
    />
  </body>
</html>
